DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     KKppaasssswwdddd is the server for the passwd(1) program.  The server provides a
     remote password changing facility with Kerberos authentication.  A user
     must provide the old Kerberos password, encrypted in a random session
     key, to the server.  KKppaasssswwdddd runs only on the Kerberos server, as it di-
     rectly updates the Kerberos database.

